text: 10 is the number of n-Queens Problem solutions for n = 5.
4 is the smallest squared prime (p2) and the only even number in this form.
January 6th is the day in 1978 that the Crown of St. Stephen (also known as the Holy Crown of Hungary) is returned to Hungary from the United States, where it was held after World War II.
3 is the first number, according to Proclus, being the first number such that n2 is greater than 2n.
